text: English Lutheran Church is a historic church at 1040 New Hampshire Street in Lawrence, Kansas. It was built in 1870, and it grew in 1900. It was added to the National Register in 1995. It is a two-story church. It is made of rusticated limestone on a limestone block base. It is about in plan.
